	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Greg2600 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I really want to see more games using the MSU1.</div><br /><br />Me too. While adding anime FMVs to games (backports from later remakes, eg Chrono Trigger) is quite difficult, adding CD-audio is actually extremely simple. Takes about 30 minutes of effort per game. Filter out routine $214x accesses that always occur, and then spot the unique ones between songs playing. Jump up a few functions in the stack and there's your &quot;lda #track; jsr loadAndPlayTrack&quot;, patch it with an MSU1 play track command, done. Brings in the possibility of adding orchestral / remix sound tracks to games and such.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


