	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">qwertymodo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">SNES programming isn't really of any use at all in terms of implementing the enhancement chips.</div><br />I don't fully agree. While <em>implementing</em> a custom chip e.g. on an FPGA might indeed be a matter of being able to program your custom hardware, accurately <em>replicating</em> the chip's behavior still requires you to understand its inner workings, its ports/registers, how it communicates with the SNES etc. In fact, I believe this is the hardest part of it all. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


